# Visualization Policy - STRICT

## CRITICAL RULE: ECharts Only
- Use ONLY Apache ECharts for ALL visualizations
- Load from CDN: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/echarts@5.4.3/dist/echarts.min.js
- NEVER use: matplotlib, seaborn, plotly, bokeh, altair, d3, chart.js, or any other charting library
- All charts must render in browser preview

## Package Approval Process
Before suggesting ANY library not in the approved list:
1. Explain why it's needed
2. Propose an alternative using ECharts or approved packages
3. Wait for explicit user approval
4. Log the request for review

## HTML Template Structure
Every visualization HTML must include:
- ECharts loaded via CDN
- Responsive container with explicit dimensions
- Chart initialization with proper options
- Window resize handler for responsiveness
- Clean, minimal styling
- Descriptive title

## ECharts Best Practices
- Use semantic option configurations
- Include interactive tooltips
- Add legends for multi-series charts
- Enable toolbox for save/zoom features
- Make charts responsive with resize listeners
- Use appropriate chart types for data

